description: Third part of the Secret De L'Espadon storyline which was initially published periodically in Le Journal De Tintin from September 26 1946 onwards. In albums, this didn't exist when the story was separated in two parts by Le Lombard in the fifties, its content being included in the previous album. When Les Editions Blake Et Mortimer took over the rights, they republished the story in three parts, this one coming out in 1986. In 2002 it was reintegrated to the two previous issues as a single all-encompassing edition.

description:
Writer SCOTT LOBDELL teams up with artist R.B. SILVA to reinvent SUPERBOY! Project N.O.W.H.E.R.E. has put a lot of effort into creating their SUPERBOY, and they intend to make sure he performs to their standards. Collecting the first seven issues of the new series!

Back Blurb

THE BOY FROM N.O.W.H.E.R.E

Superboy has been alive only three and a half months. A clone developed by the scientist as at the ultra-secret institute N.O.W.H.E.R.E., he has never left the incubation in which he was grown. Until now.

By fusing human and Kryptonian DNA, N.O.W.H.E.R.E created a living weapon. The organization and its mysterious leadership want to use Superboy and his telekinetic powers to capture other metahuman teens, like Wonder Girl and her friends. But while he spars with the likes of the Teen Titans, Supergirl and Rose Wilson, Superboy also fights his own battle within, attempting to discover what he is and who he wants to become. Supergirl and N.O.W.H.E.R.E. both think Superboy will become a killer. But can a clone develop a conscience?

From writer SCOTT LOBDELL (TEEN TITANS, RED HOOD AND THE OUTLAWS) and artist R.B. SILVA (JIMMY OLSEN), SUPERBOY: INCUBATION (collecting issues #1-7) creates a dark origin for the Boy of Steel as he uncovers more about himself and his sinister creators.
name: Volume 1

description:
The DCU’s most wanted man stars in his own new collected edition! • GRIFTER is branded a serial killer when he begins hunting and exterminating inhuman creatures hidden in human form that only he can see! With GRIFTER the only hero who can see them, it isn’t long before the DAEMONITES are out to kill him! Guest-starring GREEN ARROW! Collects GRIFTER #1-8!

Back Blurb

DCU'S MOST WANTED MAN

Cole Cash is a charming grifter few can resist. Ex-Special Oops, Cash has a certain special skill: he can spot deadly inhuman creatures hiding in plain sight in human form! As the sweet-talker hunts down these deceptive devils, the goverment brands him as a serial killer and he is forced to go on the lam.

Soon enough, the gun-wielding con man meets an array of attractive partners and discovers the true powe fo the Daemonites, a reptilian alien race that is determined to have Cash play a prominent role in their evil master plan. From New Orleans to Seattle to the Himalays, Cash uncovers world-changing secrets as adeadly as they are powerful.

GRIFTER: MOST WANTED --- collecting issues #1-8 --- features the thrilling work of writer NATHAN EDMONSON (Olymus), and artist CAFU (T.H.U.N.D.E.R. AGENTS), BIT (VIXEN), SCOTT CLARK (BRIGHTEST DAY), JASON GORDER (SUPERMAN) and DAVE BEATY (JUSTICE LEAGUE).
name: Volume 1

description:
On the ground and on the front lines, a young, headstrong soldier known as JOE ROCK assumes command of EASY COMPANY – a team of ex-military men turned contractors. From today’s battlefields come these tales of war against terrorism. Collects the entire eight-issue run of MEN OF WAR!

Back Blurb

WAR IS HELL...EVEN FOR EASY COMPANY

Josep Rock is the grandson of the World War II hero Sgt. Rock. He's a soldier's soldier, chosen for a mission outside the ordinary bounds of war. Rock and the rest of Easy Company drop into enemy territory and complete their directives with near invisibility.

Easy Company is made up of some of the finest men in the Armed Services...and yet, they are only men. But in this war, there is more to fear than just insurgents and terrorist. There are super humans who can set a whole city ablazer, mysterious immortal soldiers and even member of Rock's own team who are far more than they seem.

And if theere's one thing all these super beings have in common...it's that they're going to make Easy Company's missions --- already anything but easy --- even deadlier.

Gritty war realism meets super-heroic action in MEN OF WAR_ UNEASY COMPANY (collecting issues #1-8), courtesy of writer IVAN BRANDON (FINAL CRISIS AFTERMATH: ESCAPE) and artist TOM DERENICK (SHADOWPACT) with help from all-star creators JAMES ROBINSON, JEFF LEMIRE, MATT KINDT, J.T. KRUL, PHIL WINSLADE, SCOTT KOLINS, PATRICK SCHERBERG and others.
name: Volume 1
